description.p:
In a first aspect there is provided a device for assessing the mechanical properties of soil comprising

(i) a transverse element (16) having a soil-engaging lower face; (ii) a soil penetrating element (20) projecting downwardly beneath said lower face; (iii) means (10) for selectively urging said device to move the soil-penetrating element (20) downwardly into the soil until the lower face of the transverse element (16) engages the soil surface, and subsequently urging an angular motion; and (iv) force sensing means (34) for sensing shear forces associated with said angular motion;

characterised in that said urging means (10) is operable for selectively urging (a) said downward movement until the lower face of the transverse element (16) engages the soil surface; (b) thereafter urging further downward movement into the soil; and (c) said angular motion, wherein said angular motion is tilting of the device so that one edge region of the transverse element (16) rises while an opposite edge region descends or provides a fulcrum; and wherein there are also force sensing means (36) for sensing compression forces associated with said further downward motion.
